What is the importance of Light Reflective Value (LRV) in commercial bathrooms?

Light Reflective Value (or LRV) is a crucial consideration in commercial bathrooms around the world. LRV is "a measure of visible and usable light that is reflected from a surface when illuminated by a light source." So in commercial bathrooms, it's the colour contrast between toilet cubicle doors and the walls, vanities and the floor, grab rails/hardware and the panel colours. This difference in visual contrast makes it easier for the elderly and those with visual impairments to see and distinguish between the two objects. We'd all have to look twice if white cubicle doors and nibs were butting up against white walls! On the flip side, a charcoal cubicle door against a white wall is the contrast we're looking for.

It's important to note with woodgrain prints that the LRV result will be an average result because the colour tones in a woodgrain print can differ depending on the position of the surface measured, as opposed to a solid colour which will provide a consistent LRV result.

We've made it easy for you to calculate the LRV rating for your chosen Durasafe(R) colours. Punch the LRV of your chosen Durasafe(R) colours from our table below into our Duacube(R) LRV Calculator, and hit 'Calculate' for your result.
